title: Bucyrus Girls Tennis Awards announced
text:
Bucyrus Girls Tennis Awards announced Staff Report 4:33 p.m. EDT October 12, 2015 CONNECT TWEET LINKEDIN COMMENT EMAIL MORE 
The Bucyrus Girls Tennis Award night was held Thursday night in the Bucyrus Secondary School Media Center. The team finished with a regular season record of 8-8. Arli Hinkle and Sarah Lipscomb earned the JV first year award. Abbie Heckert earn a second year JV award. Alivia Lewis, Daniell Prederie, Cassie Hinkle and Franchisca Thompson all earned first year varsity letters. Celina Kelly, Hadley French and Loarel Mollenkopf earned their second varsity letter. Ashton Hawkins and Alyssa Mussleman earned their third varsity letter. Hawkins and Mollenkopf shared MVP honors while Mussleman won the Most Improved Award. Thompson earned the Sam Sabback Award to round out the night. Read or Share this story: http://ohne.ws/1Lr7p4a TOP VIDEOS
